1
00:01:42,669 --> 00:01:43,670
Will you marry me?

2
00:01:43,670 --> 00:01:45,228
Kabir... please.

3
00:01:45,738 --> 00:01:46,705
Okay.

4
00:01:47,507 --> 00:01:49,236
Will you marry me, please?

5
00:01:50,543 --> 00:01:51,703
Why are you doing this?

6
00:01:52,445 --> 00:01:54,345
Because sooner or later we will.

7
00:01:55,615 --> 00:01:56,980
We love each other.

8
00:01:57,684 --> 00:01:59,982
Our families seem to tolerate each other.

9
00:02:01,020 --> 00:02:03,989
I'm an architect and
you're an interior designer.

10
00:02:04,824 --> 00:02:05,848
We're perfect.

11
00:02:09,162 --> 00:02:10,220
What do you say?

12
00:02:11,764 --> 00:02:12,788
Are you sure?

13
00:02:13,533 --> 00:02:15,592
Natasha, please make it quick...

14
00:02:15,668 --> 00:02:16,396
my knee is hurting.

15
00:02:18,505 --> 00:02:19,472
Yes!

16
00:02:37,423 --> 00:02:42,053
It seems like only yesterday
that Natasha came into this world.

17
00:02:42,495 --> 00:02:43,826
And today she's getting engaged.

18
00:02:45,398 --> 00:02:47,423
Kabir, I'm not losing a daughter.

19
00:02:48,501 --> 00:02:50,025
I'm gaining a son.

20
00:02:50,603 --> 00:02:51,831
You're so filmy, dad.

21
00:02:56,709 --> 00:02:57,266
Harryji

22
00:02:59,445 --> 00:03:02,744
Two years ago you commissioned me
to build your hotel.

23
00:03:03,716 --> 00:03:06,446
Who would've imagined that
one day we'll be a big family.

24
00:03:06,920 --> 00:03:09,980
On behalf of my family,
I welcome you all.

25
00:03:10,423 --> 00:03:11,287
Thank you so much.

26
00:03:11,925 --> 00:03:15,326
Did you ever know that you're my hero

27
00:03:16,729 --> 00:03:19,789
You're everything I wish I could be

28
00:03:21,067 --> 00:03:24,264
I can fly like an eagle

29
00:03:24,771 --> 00:03:29,799
Cause you're the wind beneath my wings

30
00:03:31,110 --> 00:03:36,980
You're the wind beneath my wings

31
00:03:41,721 --> 00:03:42,847
- That was lovely.

32
00:03:48,361 --> 00:03:49,229
Hello everyone.

33
00:03:49,229 --> 00:03:50,389
I am lmran.

34
00:03:51,164 --> 00:03:52,688
Kabir and I have been friends
since school.

35
00:03:52,899 --> 00:03:54,127
The three Musketeers!

36
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:57,301
That's right, it was the name
uncle had given the three of us.

37
00:03:57,570 --> 00:03:58,537
The three Musketeers.

38
00:03:59,372 --> 00:04:01,608
Unfortunately, the third musketeer...

39
00:04:01,608 --> 00:04:03,803
Arjun is not with us anymore.

40
00:04:05,511 --> 00:04:08,503
Don't worry, he's alive.
He just isn't here right now.

41
00:04:10,683 --> 00:04:11,707
Anyway, Natasha...

42
00:04:11,985 --> 00:04:14,613
Kabir is one of the nicest guys ever.

43
00:04:15,755 --> 00:04:18,223
So, if you ever smash his BMW,
don't worry.

44
00:04:19,525 --> 00:04:20,549
Good excuse to get a new car.

45
00:04:21,995 --> 00:04:24,463
He's also very intelligent.

46
00:04:25,932 --> 00:04:27,957
So leave the kid's homework to him.

47
00:04:28,434 --> 00:04:29,769
You're a true friend, thanks.

48
00:04:29,769 --> 00:04:30,736
You're welcome, bro.

49
00:04:31,704 --> 00:04:33,569
He's very large hearted.

50
00:04:34,207 --> 00:04:36,075
So, don't think twice...

51
00:04:36,075 --> 00:04:37,702
just buy those diamonds.

52
00:04:44,183 --> 00:04:45,377
Basically Natasha...

53
00:04:45,985 --> 00:04:48,010
Kabir is a solid guy.

54
00:04:49,022 --> 00:04:51,422
Put your hand in his and
walk with him.

55
00:04:52,659 --> 00:04:54,149
Because no matter what...

56
00:04:54,394 --> 00:04:55,520
he will never let you down.

57
00:04:56,496 --> 00:04:57,986
- So sweet.
- Hear, hear!

58
00:05:00,533 --> 00:05:01,500
Thank you.

59
00:05:01,768 --> 00:05:02,666
You can send the cheque now.

60
00:05:04,771 --> 00:05:05,465
Tanya...

61
00:05:06,606 --> 00:05:07,470
thank you.

62
00:05:08,441 --> 00:05:09,840
Let me warn you...

63
00:05:10,009 --> 00:05:12,409
Nikhil is planning a
full power bachelor party.

64
00:05:12,845 --> 00:05:13,713
Too late.

65
00:05:13,713 --> 00:05:16,409
His school friends have planned
a bachelor holiday.

66
00:05:16,716 --> 00:05:17,705
A road trip...

67
00:05:17,917 --> 00:05:18,747
through Spain.

68
00:05:19,185 --> 00:05:21,050
- A road trip?
- Don't ask.

69
00:05:21,487 --> 00:05:23,990
They had made some pact
in college that...

70
00:05:23,990 --> 00:05:27,060
each one would choose
an adventure sport...

71
00:05:27,060 --> 00:05:29,085
Are you serious?
Like Fear Factor?

72
00:05:29,595 --> 00:05:30,584
Exactly!

73
00:05:30,663 --> 00:05:33,154
And the other two would have to do it.

74
00:05:33,900 --> 00:05:35,094
So, what have you picked?

75
00:05:35,702 --> 00:05:37,067
That I can't say.

76
00:05:38,237 --> 00:05:39,636
Not in front of me, at least.

77
00:05:40,940 --> 00:05:41,838
You see...

78
00:05:41,908 --> 00:05:45,139
the sport we pick
is a surprise for the other two.

79
00:05:45,611 --> 00:05:46,600
Shut up!

80
00:05:46,846 --> 00:05:48,211
- Seriously.
- Are you kidding me?

81
00:05:48,581 --> 00:05:49,570
No.

82
00:05:49,882 --> 00:05:52,749
That ensures none of us back out.

83
00:05:53,753 --> 00:05:55,243
Whose idea was this?

84
00:05:55,755 --> 00:05:56,414
Mine.

85
00:05:57,156 --> 00:05:57,850
Three weeks.

86
00:05:58,057 --> 00:05:59,388
You know how these boys are.

87
00:05:59,926 --> 00:06:00,449
Not Kabir.

88
00:06:01,260 --> 00:06:02,420
Oh please!

89
00:06:02,762 --> 00:06:05,322
All guys go crazy at bachelor parties.

90
00:06:06,432 --> 00:06:07,626
In fact...

91
00:06:07,700 --> 00:06:12,433
Nikhil still hasn't told me
what happened at his.

92
00:06:13,873 --> 00:06:14,737
I don't know.

93
00:06:15,575 --> 00:06:18,135
I heard something about
your bachelor party.

94
00:06:23,750 --> 00:06:24,614
Who told you?

95
00:06:24,884 --> 00:06:25,851
So it is true.

96
00:06:26,853 --> 00:06:27,751
Does Natasha know?

97
00:06:28,755 --> 00:06:29,949
No man, why would I tell her?

98
00:06:30,256 --> 00:06:31,746
Please... don't tell her.

99
00:06:33,493 --> 00:06:34,482
She was from Ukraine.

100
00:06:35,928 --> 00:06:37,259
- Bloody hot!
- Nice.

101
00:06:37,663 --> 00:06:38,527
I was sloshed.

102
00:06:40,099 --> 00:06:41,123
Okay, listen...

103
00:06:41,501 --> 00:06:43,992
If Sameera finds out about this,
she'll kill me.

104
00:06:44,570 --> 00:06:45,969
I know, don't worry.

105
00:06:46,038 --> 00:06:49,208
It was my last night as a bachelor.
You know I'd never do it otherwise.

106
00:06:49,208 --> 00:06:51,244
I understand, don't worry about it.

107
00:06:51,244 --> 00:06:52,233
- Please.
- It happens.

108
00:06:53,846 --> 00:06:54,813
Sameera!

109
00:06:58,317 --> 00:06:59,375
Sorry, I couldn't resist.

110
00:07:00,219 --> 00:07:02,084
- Take care, man.
- See you.

111
00:07:05,057 --> 00:07:07,855
Trust me, this trick never fails.

112
00:07:08,327 --> 00:07:09,929
What do you mean?

113
00:07:09,929 --> 00:07:14,457
Well, you tell people you know
something about them...

114
00:07:14,534 --> 00:07:17,737
and before you know it,
they tell you their secrets.

115
00:07:17,737 --> 00:07:19,071
Shut up!

116
00:07:19,071 --> 00:07:21,266
You didn't know about the Ukrainian?

117
00:07:21,674 --> 00:07:23,039
No, he just told me.

118
00:07:24,377 --> 00:07:26,038
Mind blowing!

119
00:07:28,381 --> 00:07:31,214
- Yeah, well time equals money, Simon.
You want money, stop wasting my time.

120
00:07:31,918 --> 00:07:33,818
Sell 50,000 June contracts!

121
00:07:33,886 --> 00:07:36,116
50,000 and don't screw up
my stop losses this time!

122
00:07:37,323 --> 00:07:38,153
How much?

123
00:07:39,325 --> 00:07:40,690
Damn! That's horrendous!

124
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:42,657
Sell it. Sell everything.

125
00:07:50,336 --> 00:07:52,538
Listen Joe, if you continue to give me
bullshit fills like that...

126
00:07:52,538 --> 00:07:54,665
I'm going to have to trade
my Ferrari in for a Ford Fiesta!

127
00:07:57,710 --> 00:07:59,871
We have white and gold and...

128
00:08:00,379 --> 00:08:01,607
tonnes of champagne.

129
00:08:02,114 --> 00:08:02,944
And...

130
00:08:04,016 --> 00:08:05,244
- the centre peice.
- This is nice.

131
00:08:06,219 --> 00:08:07,117
Finally!

132
00:08:07,687 --> 00:08:08,381
Kabira!

133
00:08:08,855 --> 00:08:10,413
Sorry man.

134
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:12,219
You have no idea what's happening here.

135
00:08:12,391 --> 00:08:14,552
And you have no idea
what a nice party you missed.

136
00:08:15,495 --> 00:08:16,723
I'm sure, man.

137
00:08:17,196 --> 00:08:18,220
Listen...

138
00:08:18,698 --> 00:08:19,926
I've a problem.

139
00:08:20,666 --> 00:08:22,201
I can't make it to Spain.

140
00:08:22,201 --> 00:08:22,724
- What?!

141
00:08:24,003 --> 00:08:25,505
Arjun, you promised!

142
00:08:25,505 --> 00:08:27,273
I know but...

143
00:08:27,273 --> 00:08:30,299
I thought this deal I'm working on
would come through...

144
00:08:30,443 --> 00:08:31,102
- but I'm stuck.

145
00:08:31,711 --> 00:08:34,509
I can't believe you're ditching me
on my bachelor trip.

146
00:08:35,515 --> 00:08:36,816
It's not that...

147
00:08:36,816 --> 00:08:38,181
- Then what is it?

148
00:08:38,417 --> 00:08:40,908
We had decided to do this together.

149
00:08:42,688 --> 00:08:45,054
If you can't make it,
I'm calling it off.

150
00:08:45,391 --> 00:08:47,621
Don't get sentimental.
It's my work!

151
00:08:47,860 --> 00:08:49,395
I'm not.

152
00:08:49,395 --> 00:08:52,265
It's been cancelled once before,
so let's do it again.

153
00:08:52,265 --> 00:08:53,562
It's fine.

154
00:08:54,934 --> 00:08:58,392
It's either the three of us going
or none at all.

155
00:09:22,495 --> 00:09:23,553
Hey...

156
00:09:24,530 --> 00:09:25,258
Hi.

157
00:09:25,498 --> 00:09:26,157
How are you?

158
00:09:26,666 --> 00:09:27,530
Good.

159
00:09:28,935 --> 00:09:30,903
Looking good,
you've been working out?

160
00:09:31,437 --> 00:09:31,994
Yes.

161
00:09:32,538 --> 00:09:34,028
I usually come in the morning.

162
00:09:39,345 --> 00:09:41,176
I was going to call you.

163
00:09:42,081 --> 00:09:43,070
Then why didn't you?

164
00:09:44,650 --> 00:09:46,015
I'm getting married.

165
00:09:50,222 --> 00:09:52,747
- That was quick.
- Arjun, please!

166
00:09:57,663 --> 00:09:58,994
All the best, Rohini.

167
00:10:16,582 --> 00:10:18,516
- Arjun, it's me again.

168
00:10:19,018 --> 00:10:20,920
- Don't ditch me.

169
00:10:20,920 --> 00:10:23,411
- I know why you're making excuses.

170
00:10:24,056 --> 00:10:26,058
- But it's been four years
for that incident.

171
00:10:26,058 --> 00:10:27,047
- I'm getting married now.

172
00:10:28,060 --> 00:10:30,255
- Even today, I only have two friends.

173
00:10:31,230 --> 00:10:34,529
- We're the three Musketeers.
All for one, one for all.

174
00:10:40,740 --> 00:10:42,298
Have you thought about...

175
00:10:43,542 --> 00:10:44,566
what we spoke?

176
00:10:45,378 --> 00:10:46,003
About what?

177
00:10:47,613 --> 00:10:50,741
Are you moving back to Bombay?

178
00:10:51,350 --> 00:10:52,339
Ammi...

179
00:10:53,185 --> 00:10:56,154
I like Delhi and living on my own.

180
00:11:02,862 --> 00:11:05,765
And this trip to Spain...

181
00:11:05,765 --> 00:11:08,427
is it a coincidence or
did you plan it?

182
00:11:10,670 --> 00:11:13,070
Why don't you just say
what you're really thinking?

183
00:11:14,573 --> 00:11:15,540
Fine.

184
00:11:16,709 --> 00:11:18,336
Do you intend to meet Salman?

185
00:11:19,612 --> 00:11:21,113
I don't know.

186
00:11:21,113 --> 00:11:23,138
Imran, why don't you trust me?

187
00:11:23,816 --> 00:11:25,551
It's not about you Ammi.

188
00:11:25,551 --> 00:11:27,920
- He is my father.
- He's your father?

189
00:11:27,920 --> 00:11:33,085
Has he ever called you
or tried to find out how you are?

190
00:11:33,159 --> 00:11:35,150
Maybe he did and
you kept it from me.

191
00:11:36,662 --> 00:11:39,028
Until recently I wasrt even aware
that he is my father.

192
00:11:40,399 --> 00:11:41,423
Alright.

193
00:11:41,667 --> 00:11:43,169
Do what you want.

194
00:11:43,169 --> 00:11:45,705
But please remember this.

195
00:11:45,705 --> 00:11:47,730
Faisal was your only father.

196
00:11:53,779 --> 00:11:55,906
- Hello there.
- Hello.

197
00:11:56,348 --> 00:11:57,683
I can see you.

198
00:11:57,683 --> 00:11:59,852
I miss you, baby.

199
00:11:59,852 --> 00:12:02,343
Now we can see each other everyday.

200
00:12:02,588 --> 00:12:05,056
I'm only going for
three weeks, Natasha.

201
00:12:13,833 --> 00:12:16,131
What will I do in London all alone?

202
00:12:16,569 --> 00:12:18,771
You'll shop.

203
00:12:18,771 --> 00:12:22,969
And in three weeks I'll come to London
to carry your shopping bags.

204
00:12:23,042 --> 00:12:25,033
- Very funny.
- I know.

205
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:10,069
- I don't see Madrid in this plan.
- Because it's not there.

206
00:16:10,069 --> 00:16:11,934
- We travel to Spain but
we're not going to see the capital?

207
00:16:12,004 --> 00:16:14,073
- We don't have enough time.

208
00:16:14,073 --> 00:16:15,768
- We can't change it now.
- I think we should.

209
00:16:15,841 --> 00:16:17,172
Look who's here!

210
00:16:18,510 --> 00:16:20,671
- Welcome! How was your flight?
- Hello.

211
00:16:21,714 --> 00:16:22,948
Well...

212
00:16:22,948 --> 00:16:24,142
it flew.

213
00:16:24,550 --> 00:16:25,744
Funny!

214
00:16:34,326 --> 00:16:36,895
- Good to see you.
- You too.

215
00:16:36,895 --> 00:16:37,953
I'm sorry about Abu.

216
00:16:38,831 --> 00:16:40,458
I got your email.

217
00:16:41,567 --> 00:16:43,262
- How's Ammi?
- She's fine.

218
00:16:43,836 --> 00:16:46,066
It's not easy to get over these things.

219
00:16:47,506 --> 00:16:48,495
How've you been?

220
00:16:48,874 --> 00:16:49,772
I'm good.

221
00:16:49,842 --> 00:16:51,176
Pretty good actually.

222
00:16:51,176 --> 00:16:53,303
I've a new apartment.
Three bedrooms, big space.

223
00:16:54,046 --> 00:16:55,047
Nice.

224
00:16:55,047 --> 00:16:57,349
I can't believe we're together again.

225
00:16:57,349 --> 00:16:59,044
- Yeah.
- Finally!

226
00:16:59,418 --> 00:17:00,316
Should we sit?

227
00:17:01,353 --> 00:17:03,184
So, here is the plan.

228
00:17:03,689 --> 00:17:04,890
First...

229
00:17:04,890 --> 00:17:07,450
we go to Costa Brava,
which is my choice.

230
00:17:08,327 --> 00:17:10,056
Then Arjun wants to go to Seville.

231
00:17:10,696 --> 00:17:12,097
And then we'll head to...

232
00:17:12,097 --> 00:17:13,621
Pampalona which you've chosen.

233
00:17:13,699 --> 00:17:15,894
Tomorrow morning we leave for
Costa Brava.

234
00:17:22,441 --> 00:17:23,669
What are you doing with the laptop?

235
00:17:24,209 --> 00:17:25,577
I'm looking for an address.

236
00:17:25,577 --> 00:17:26,874
Hola Kabira.

237
00:17:30,249 --> 00:17:31,739
Kabira...

238
00:17:32,151 --> 00:17:33,209
Your treasure.

239
00:17:34,420 --> 00:17:36,115
Brilliant. Thanks a ton.

240
00:17:40,325 --> 00:17:41,986
What have you done to this?

241
00:17:42,394 --> 00:17:43,452
Dude!

242
00:17:43,529 --> 00:17:47,199
First of all, be thankful that
I bought this 12,000 Euro bag for you!

243
00:17:47,199 --> 00:17:48,097
What?

244
00:17:49,568 --> 00:17:50,227
Here... show, show...

245
00:17:54,840 --> 00:17:56,671
12,000 Euro for this purse?

246
00:17:57,176 --> 00:17:58,507
Way more than your salary.

247
00:18:01,914 --> 00:18:02,471
What?

248
00:18:03,649 --> 00:18:05,139
Natasha loves these bags.

249
00:18:05,584 --> 00:18:06,812
And I love cars, Kabir.

250
00:18:07,586 --> 00:18:08,780
Always remember.

251
00:18:08,854 --> 00:18:10,913
If you ever want to gift
me an expensive car...

252
00:18:10,989 --> 00:18:12,658
don't hesitate.

253
00:18:12,658 --> 00:18:14,093
I won't.

254
00:18:14,093 --> 00:18:14,616
Good.

255
00:18:14,693 --> 00:18:15,694
Let's go.

256
00:18:15,694 --> 00:18:17,025
I can't.

257
00:18:17,763 --> 00:18:19,598
I need to make some calls.

258
00:18:19,598 --> 00:18:20,394
I'll see you guys later.

259
00:18:21,834 --> 00:18:23,199
Adios amigos.

260
00:18:24,369 --> 00:18:26,564
- I thought this was a holiday.
- Me too.

261
00:18:27,272 --> 00:18:28,933
Let's go.

262
00:18:29,208 --> 00:18:30,175
We take the next right.

263
00:18:34,346 --> 00:18:35,813
- Looks quite old.
- There it is.

264
00:18:39,751 --> 00:18:40,911
There is the cathedral.

265
00:18:42,254 --> 00:18:44,313
- Do you know where this place is?
- Yes, straight ahead.

266
00:18:44,723 --> 00:18:46,213
How far is this gallery?

267
00:18:47,059 --> 00:18:48,026
Shut up!

268
00:18:48,360 --> 00:18:49,657
It's just here.

269
00:18:50,329 --> 00:18:52,729
This is the street.
Catonia... whatever.

270
00:18:54,766 --> 00:18:55,960
And that's the place.

271
00:18:56,034 --> 00:18:57,194
I guess.

272
00:19:09,014 --> 00:19:10,208
Hey!

273
00:19:14,219 --> 00:19:15,777
