it would've been a bit strange.

380
00:34:10,943 --> 00:34:12,342
- You've got bail.

381
00:34:15,615 --> 00:34:16,912
They're here.

382
00:34:28,628 --> 00:34:29,492
Hi.

383
00:34:32,532 --> 00:34:33,328
Imran.

384
00:34:35,535 --> 00:34:36,502
Imran...

385
00:34:37,770 --> 00:34:38,634
I'm Salman.

386
00:34:43,309 --> 00:34:45,378
My friends, Arjun and Kabir.

387
00:34:45,378 --> 00:34:46,572
- Hello.
- Thank you.

388
00:34:46,646 --> 00:34:47,943
Hi... thank you.

389
00:34:48,881 --> 00:34:50,872
You three look pretty hungover.

390
00:34:54,187 --> 00:34:56,985
You're welcome to come over to
my place and freshen up.

391
00:34:57,657 --> 00:35:00,387
Our bags and car are at the hotel.

392
00:35:00,593 --> 00:35:01,992
I'll drive you there.

393
00:35:03,830 --> 00:35:04,524
Come.

394
00:35:19,512 --> 00:35:21,537
- Wow, this is beautiful.

395
00:35:23,282 --> 00:35:24,306
It's really nice.

396
00:35:25,518 --> 00:35:27,713
Are you always so polite?

397
00:35:29,188 --> 00:35:32,487
It's absolute rubbish.
Anyone can do that.

398
00:35:33,292 --> 00:35:35,795
This gentleman, my neighbour...

399
00:35:35,795 --> 00:35:38,998
was obsessed with having his wife
immortalised in a potrait.

400
00:35:38,998 --> 00:35:42,525
So, I applied my brush
and fulfilled his desire.

401
00:35:42,602 --> 00:35:44,934
And with his money, paid my bills.

402
00:35:47,306 --> 00:35:49,638
So, what are you guys doing in Seville?

403
00:35:50,343 --> 00:35:51,711
Skydiving.

404
00:35:51,711 --> 00:35:52,871
- Really?
- Yeah.

405
00:35:52,945 --> 00:35:55,072
So, you jumped out of a plane
and landed in jail?

406
00:35:56,349 --> 00:35:57,714
You could say that.

407
00:35:58,184 --> 00:36:02,314
That apart, what do you do?

408
00:36:03,289 --> 00:36:04,916
Well, I'm a financial broker.

409
00:36:05,291 --> 00:36:06,258
In London.

410
00:36:06,759 --> 00:36:07,817
Money man.

411
00:36:09,262 --> 00:36:09,990
And you?

412
00:36:10,630 --> 00:36:12,325
My family is in the construction business.

413
00:36:13,366 --> 00:36:15,732
Well, never mind.
Everyone makes mistakes.

414
00:36:16,702 --> 00:36:17,498
That's funny.

415
00:36:18,137 --> 00:36:20,128
You're a Xerox copy of him.

416
00:36:23,843 --> 00:36:25,538
And, what about you?

417
00:36:26,946 --> 00:36:27,844
I write.

418
00:36:29,515 --> 00:36:30,072
What?

419
00:36:30,950 --> 00:36:32,679
I'm a copywriter in advertising.

420
00:36:33,753 --> 00:36:36,813
Writing copy for ads is like
a buffet for the masses.

421
00:36:37,190 --> 00:36:39,886
For instance, this painting is
for someone else.

422
00:36:41,327 --> 00:36:44,125
Do you write anything
to feed your own soul?

423
00:36:45,831 --> 00:36:47,162
I do.

424
00:36:51,971 --> 00:36:52,460
Sir?

425
00:36:52,838 --> 00:36:53,668
Salman.

426
00:36:54,373 --> 00:36:56,102
Right. We'll be outside.

427
00:37:13,593 --> 00:37:16,756
Your hands are very similar to mine.

428
00:37:20,166 --> 00:37:21,133
Sit.

429
00:37:24,870 --> 00:37:25,768
Do you live alone?

430
00:37:26,272 --> 00:37:27,239
No.

431
00:37:27,940 --> 00:37:28,804
I have a wife.

432
00:37:29,175 --> 00:37:31,302
But she is away... in Paris.

433
00:37:31,811 --> 00:37:32,505
Sit.

434
00:37:35,615 --> 00:37:36,547
And any...

435
00:37:36,782 --> 00:37:37,942
children?

436
00:37:44,523 --> 00:37:45,751
Do you ever come to India?

437
00:37:46,792 --> 00:37:47,860
Yes.

438
00:37:47,860 --> 00:37:50,727
I was there four years ago
when my mother passed away.

439
00:37:52,098 --> 00:37:53,799
- Sorry.
- I have a brother there...

440
00:37:53,799 --> 00:37:54,766
but...

441
00:37:56,369 --> 00:37:57,666
we don't meet.

442
00:38:03,276 --> 00:38:05,642
I've often thought about you.

443
00:38:07,613 --> 00:38:08,637
I mean...

444
00:38:10,116 --> 00:38:14,576
that someday, somewhere we might meet.

445
00:38:16,255 --> 00:38:18,691
But I never figured...

446
00:38:18,691 --> 00:38:21,251
what I would say to you.

447
00:38:22,928 --> 00:38:24,088
Just say the truth.

448
00:38:26,866 --> 00:38:29,061
The truth... what is the truth?

449
00:38:30,303 --> 00:38:32,863
Everyone has their own version.

450
00:38:38,210 --> 00:38:40,379
Look... I was...

451
00:38:40,379 --> 00:38:42,244
25 then.

452
00:38:43,416 --> 00:38:46,385
Rahila was a few years younger.

453
00:38:47,787 --> 00:38:50,523
When you're young
the future doesn't matter.

454
00:38:50,523 --> 00:38:52,150
We were just kids.

455
00:38:54,794 --> 00:38:56,853
One day...

456
00:38:56,929 --> 00:38:59,420
Rahila told me that she's...

457
00:39:00,032 --> 00:39:02,899
expecting a baby.

458
00:39:02,968 --> 00:39:05,869
I wasrt ready for
the responsibility then.

459
00:39:05,938 --> 00:39:07,838
And nor am I now.

460
00:39:14,347 --> 00:39:17,282
So... you just abandoned her?

461
00:39:21,153 --> 00:39:24,145
I guess, you could say that.

462
00:39:29,328 --> 00:39:33,856
Rahila wanted a family,
she wanted to be a mother.

463
00:39:35,167 --> 00:39:37,795
I had other dreams.
I wanted to be an artist.

464
00:39:38,804 --> 00:39:40,806
I wanted to paint...

465
00:39:40,806 --> 00:39:42,273
travel the world.

466
00:39:43,809 --> 00:39:46,212
I loved her but...

467
00:39:46,212 --> 00:39:49,238
she made her choice
and I made mine.

468
00:39:49,315 --> 00:39:51,112
That's all.

469
00:39:55,020 --> 00:39:57,250
I found out about you
only last year.

470
00:40:01,193 --> 00:40:02,160
But...

471
00:40:03,863 --> 00:40:06,491
you've always known about me.

472
00:40:08,334 --> 00:40:10,996
Did you never want to see me?

473
00:40:13,139 --> 00:40:15,039
I thought it was better this way.

474
00:40:23,015 --> 00:40:25,506
You asked for the truth.

475
00:40:26,919 --> 00:40:28,045
Well, this is it.

476
00:40:30,790 --> 00:40:32,155
I... am sorry, lmran.

477
00:40:34,093 --> 00:40:35,117
No, you're not.

478
00:40:40,032 --> 00:40:42,432
Is there something
I can do for you?

479
00:40:44,003 --> 00:40:46,995
Apologise only when it comes from here.

480
00:41:10,262 --> 00:41:13,231
When clouds of pain loom in the sky

481
00:41:13,933 --> 00:41:16,902
When a shadow of sadness flickers by

482
00:41:17,703 --> 00:41:20,672
When a tear flnds it's way to the eye

483
00:41:21,040 --> 00:41:24,009
When fear keeps the loneliness alive

484
00:41:25,010 --> 00:41:29,648
I try and console my heart
Why is it that you cry? I ask

485
00:41:29,648 --> 00:41:32,173
This is only what life imparts

486
00:41:32,918 --> 00:41:35,318
These deep silences within

487
00:41:35,821 --> 00:41:38,449
Have been handed out to all by time

488
00:41:39,692 --> 00:41:42,183
Everyone's story has a little sorrow

489
00:41:42,761 --> 00:41:45,423
Everyone's share has a little Sunshine

490
00:41:46,799 --> 00:41:48,858
No need for water in your eyes

491
00:41:50,269 --> 00:41:52,567
Every moment can be a new life

492
00:41:53,973 --> 00:41:56,168
Why do you let them pass you by

493
00:41:57,643 --> 00:41:59,611
Oh heart, why is it that you cry?

494
00:42:08,854 --> 00:42:10,014
Morning...

495
00:42:16,262 --> 00:42:17,286
Did you sleep or not?

496
00:42:18,931 --> 00:42:19,659
No.

497
00:42:28,841 --> 00:42:31,469
I think, we should get going.

498
00:42:33,178 --> 00:42:34,167
Let's go.

499
00:42:35,614 --> 00:42:36,239
Arjun...

500
00:42:40,419 --> 00:42:42,250
I'm really sorry.

501
00:43:07,146 --> 00:43:08,204
I'll see you at the car.

502
00:43:08,447 --> 00:43:09,277
Yeah.

503
00:43:13,419 --> 00:43:15,319
What do you mean,
'you slept in the car'?

504
00:43:16,088 --> 00:43:17,385
Long story, babe.

505
00:43:18,457 --> 00:43:19,481
Tell me, what happened?

506
00:43:20,759 --> 00:43:22,727
Well, lmran just...

507
00:43:24,663 --> 00:43:25,823
I'll tell you later, okay.

508
00:43:26,699 --> 00:43:28,428
Why? Tell me now,
what happened?

509
00:43:28,767 --> 00:43:31,736
I can't tell you right now.
I'll tell you when I'm back.

510
00:43:32,104 --> 00:43:33,571
Why are you getting irritated?

511
00:43:33,839 --> 00:43:35,704
Why are you going on about it?

512
00:43:35,941 --> 00:43:37,238
Okay, forget it.

513
00:43:41,680 --> 00:43:42,612
See.

514
00:43:42,982 --> 00:43:44,609
It's our wedding card.
Can you see it?

515
00:43:45,017 --> 00:43:46,416
Isn't it gorgeous?

516
00:43:46,952 --> 00:43:48,579
I'm just so happy with it.

517
00:43:49,421 --> 00:43:52,024
Oh... I've emailed a few options
for your suit.

518
00:43:52,024 --> 00:43:54,720
Please select one. Okay?
Don't forget.

519
00:43:55,194 --> 00:43:56,092
Okay.

520
00:43:58,330 --> 00:44:00,525
You are so far away.

521
00:44:01,834 --> 00:44:03,301
You love me, right?

522
00:44:04,670 --> 00:44:05,637
Yeah.

523
00:44:06,338 --> 00:44:08,203
Then stop fighting with me.

524
00:44:09,041 --> 00:44:12,169
Everything was fine before you
went on this holiday.

525
00:44:12,845 --> 00:44:14,642
Kabir, just come home.

526
00:44:15,147 --> 00:44:18,583
To me, your family, your friends.

527
00:44:18,984 --> 00:44:20,781
My friends are with me.

528
00:44:21,086 --> 00:44:23,054
Yeah, I know.
But you know what I mean.

529
00:44:34,633 --> 00:44:41,539
Happy birthday to you...

530
00:44:42,508 --> 00:44:46,137
Happy birthday dear Anjali...

531
00:44:46,812 --> 00:44:49,337
Happy birthday to you...

532
00:44:55,988 --> 00:44:56,886
Oh my God!

533
00:44:57,923 --> 00:44:59,117
It's beautiful!

534
00:44:59,491 --> 00:45:00,549
- Nice, right?
- Yes!

535
00:45:02,661 --> 00:45:03,525
Tanya?

536
00:45:13,672 --> 00:45:14,832
What are you doing, baby?

537
00:45:15,441 --> 00:45:16,840
I'm sorry, I'm so happy.

538
00:45:17,309 --> 00:45:19,539
Kabir just proposed to Natasha.

539
00:45:19,611 --> 00:45:20,846
- What??

540
00:45:20,846 --> 00:45:22,848
Oh my God!

541
00:45:22,848 --> 00:45:25,517
You could've waited until
your mother had cut the cake.

542
00:45:25,517 --> 00:45:28,509
Kabir, this is the best birthday gift, ever!

543
00:45:28,587 --> 00:45:29,688
I love you, son.

544
00:45:29,688 --> 00:45:30,746
- The shy guy!

545
00:45:31,423 --> 00:45:33,525
- It's a double celebration.

546
00:45:33,525 --> 00:45:34,992
I'm so happy.

547
00:45:35,761 --> 00:45:36,750
Now you have to call me 'mummy'.

548
00:45:38,263 --> 00:45:40,128
- Get some champagne!

549
00:45:42,835 --> 00:45:43,324
Come here.

550
00:45:45,838 --> 00:45:47,237
Very good decision.

551
00:45:49,475 --> 00:45:51,443
I'm so happy.

552
00:45:52,711 --> 00:45:55,236
Babe, what just happened in there?

553
00:45:55,314 --> 00:45:57,612
- What do you mean?
- I mean...

554
00:45:58,117 --> 00:45:59,852
This ring...

555
00:45:59,852 --> 00:46:01,251
I got it for my mom.

556
00:46:03,255 --> 00:46:05,052
It's her birthday gift.

557
00:46:05,657 --> 00:46:06,715
This is for your mom?

558
00:46:07,359 --> 00:46:10,226
Look at it sweety...
it's a mummy ring.

559
00:46:10,295 --> 00:46:11,697
What?

560
00:46:11,697 --> 00:46:13,062
Why didn't you say something?

561
00:46:13,532 --> 00:46:15,056
I tried.

562
00:46:15,134 --> 00:46:19,036
But you were excited and screaming.
And Tanya made an announcement.

563
00:46:19,705 --> 00:46:21,866
So you don't want to marry me?

564
00:46:22,307 --> 00:46:25,834
It's not about you.
I haven't even thought about marriage.

565
00:46:28,514 --> 00:46:30,311
What do I tell my father?

566
00:46:35,287 --> 00:46:38,190
We'll say that
we gave it some more thought and...

567
00:46:38,190 --> 00:46:40,590
we need more time.
That's all.

568
00:46:40,659 --> 00:46:42,286
This is so embarrassing.

569
00:46:43,128 --> 00:46:45,187
I'm so sorry, sweety.

570
00:46:46,131 --> 00:46:48,827
You don't ever want to marry me?

571
00:46:50,102 --> 00:46:51,937
It's not like that.

572
00:46:51,937 --> 00:46:54,462
If it is, you better tell me right now!

573
00:46:55,774 --> 00:46:58,477
I really love you, Kabir.
And I don't...

574
00:46:58,477 --> 00:47:01,708
No, no... no sweety.
Don't cry.

575
00:47:01,780 --> 00:47:02,712
Not now.

576
00:47:10,088 --> 00:47:10,816
Kabir...

577
00:47:12,758 --> 00:47:16,455
are you even serious
about this relationship or not?

578
00:47:19,798 --> 00:47:20,628
You know what...

579
00:47:31,677 --> 00:47:32,701
Will you marry me?

580
00:47:56,835 --> 00:47:57,893
Who is it?

581
00:48:12,784 --> 00:48:13,648
Room service.

582
00:48:14,853 --> 00:48:15,478
Laila?

583
00:48:16,521 --> 00:48:17,545
Hi!

584
00:48:17,623 --> 00:48:18,453
Oh my God!

585
00:48:19,858 --> 00:48:21,325
You're here... how... I mean...

586
00:48:21,760 --> 00:48:24,456
Imran called and
he begged me to come.

587
00:48:24,796 --> 00:48:25,990
- So I came.
- Imran?

588
00:48:26,465 --> 00:48:27,489
I knew it.

589
00:48:28,166 --> 00:48:29,724
He is my best friend.

590
00:48:32,871 --> 00:48:35,032
I am... so glad you're here.

591
00:48:36,475 --> 00:48:38,136
I'm glad you are glad.

592
00:48:40,812 --> 00:48:42,973
Hello... my the two the love the birds!

593
00:48:43,448 --> 00:48:44,779
Hello!

594
00:48:44,917 --> 00:48:45,975
Surprised, Arjun?

595
00:48:47,286 --> 00:48:48,344
Thank you.

596
00:48:48,420 --> 00:48:49,821
It's good to see you.

597
00:48:49,821 --> 00:48:51,015
- And you.
- Hey gorgeous.

598
00:48:51,089 --> 00:48:53,158
- I love you too.
- Nice to have you back.

599
00:48:53,158 --> 00:48:54,523
You got a tan!

600
00:48:55,294 --> 00:48:56,295
Get dressed, soon!

601
00:48:56,295 --> 00:48:57,629
- We had to leave at seven.
- Correct.

602
00:48:57,629 --> 00:48:58,830
- Two minutes?
- You missed me?

603
00:48:58,830 --> 00:49:00,499
I always miss you, darling.

604
00:49:00,499 --> 00:49:01,523
Where are we going?

605
00:49:01,600 --> 00:49:03,227
It's a surprise.
Can't tell you in front of him.

606
00:49:21,286 --> 00:49:22,446
What's going on?

607
00:49:22,854 --> 00:49:23,912
What do you mean?

608
00:49:24,156 --> 00:49:25,214
It's San Fermin.

609
00:49:25,290 --> 00:49:26,325
Running with the bulls.

610
00:49:26,325 --> 00:49:27,724
- Really?
- Didrt you know?

611
00:49:27,793 --> 00:49:28,919
Just follow me...

612
00:49:37,202 --> 00:49:38,260
Holy shit!

613
00:49:45,310 --> 00:49:46,937
Are these guys mad?
What are they doing?

614
00:49:47,179 --> 00:49:47,975
Suicide.

615
00:49:48,513 --> 00:49:49,878
Isn't that why you are here?

616
00:50:00,592 --> 00:50:02,651
I felt this should be the
last experience of our trip.

617
00:50:03,362 --> 00:50:05,830
This could be the
last experience of our life!

618
00:50:06,164 --> 00:50:08,333
Stop it, Arjun.
Let's grab a bite.

619
00:50:08,333 --> 00:50:08,890
Come on.

620
00:50:09,968 --> 00:50:11,036
- Excuse me.
- Dude are you...

621
00:50:11,036 --> 00:50:12,264
- I'm starving!

622
00:50:13,872 --> 00:50:15,362
This is not an adventure sport.

623
00:50:16,041 --> 00:50:17,338
I object, Judge sahab!

624
00:50:17,976 --> 00:50:20,145
I agree it's not as safe as regular sports.

625
00:50:20,145 --> 00:50:21,713
And is illegal in some countries.

626
00:50:21,713 --> 00:50:24,511
But according to the
Spanish tradition and culture...

627
00:50:24,583 --> 00:50:25,517
it is allowed.

628
00:50:25,517 --> 00:50:27,508
And technically,
according to our deal...

629
00:50:27,586 --> 00:50:29,986
we can choose any sport, remember?

630
00:50:30,322 --> 00:50:31,823
Lmran, it's really dangerous, you know.

631
00:50:31,823 --> 00:50:34,018
Yes, those bulls could kill us, alright?

632
00:50:34,259 --> 00:50:36,928
We'll be dangling on their horns
like tandoori chicken on skewers!

633
00:50:36,928 --> 00:50:38,657
Precisely the point.

634
00:50:39,798 --> 00:50:41,857
You want to get rid of
the fear within you?

635
00:50:42,134 --> 00:50:44,295
Well then, here's
our deepest fear. Death.

636
00:50:45,337 --> 00:50:46,361
Let's face it.

637
00:50:46,972 --> 00:50:48,340
Because beyond this fear...

638
00:50:48,340 --> 00:50:49,238
lies victory!

639
00:50:49,307 --> 00:50:51,332
Please spare us the tag lines!

640
00:50:51,777 --> 00:50:53,472
Dude, think about it!

641
00:50:53,712 --> 00:50:57,341
No training, no instructors.
Just us, my amigos!

642
00:50:58,083 --> 00:50:59,880
And some bulls running after us.

643
00:51:00,118 --> 00:51:02,416
If you want to live... just run!

644
00:51:02,821 --> 00:51:04,982
Laila, do you know
any psychiatrist around here?

645
00:51:05,757 --> 00:51:07,987
Because our amigo has
completely lost it!

646
00:51:08,827 --> 00:51:10,852
I'll be at the starting line
at seven tomorrow morning.

647
00:51:11,496 --> 00:51:13,464
With or without you.

648
00:51:19,004 --> 00:51:19,404
I have something for you, lmran.

649
00:51:19,404 --> 00:51:20,393
I have something for you, lmran.

650
00:51:21,273 --> 00:51:22,103
It's from Nuria.

651
00:51:25,877 --> 00:51:26,673
It's in Spanish.

652
00:51:27,646 --> 00:51:28,908
